[OW] OWASP TOP 10 BASIC AUTOMATED CHECK - supplementary to [O] Security Hardening
  This is a lightweight automated supplement to check [O]. It does NOT
  replace the full LLM adversarial review in [O].

  1. Search source code for common OWASP patterns:
     - Hardcoded secrets/passwords/API keys -> flag any matches
     - SQL string concatenation (not parameterized) -> flag any matches
     - eval(), exec(), or dynamic function calls -> flag any matches
     - InnerHTML, document.write(), or equivalent DOM sinks -> flag any matches

  2. For backend-api tasks:
     - Verify CORS configuration does not include wildcard (*) origins
     - Verify rate limiting is configured on auth endpoints
     - Verify CSRF protection is enabled if using cookie-based auth

  3. For frontend-feature tasks:
     - Verify CSP headers are configured
     - Verify no sensitive data stored in localStorage

  For each item: PASS, FAIL, or N/A.
  For every FAIL: fix the issue. Do not proceed until all PASS or N/A.

  Print: "OWASP BASIC: [N] checks passed, [N] issues fixed"
